commitResults.messageBody:
* Add javaDocs for new methods created for GUI-Level-10
* Checkstyle for Java Tests
* JavaDocs for Java Tests inclusive of testing methods

* Tasklist - mark, unmark and reset methods, check after each
command that the tasklist/task is in the appropriate state
*Parser and storage - at each stage check that the inputs and their
length is appropriate for parsing

For Parser class, abstract multiple deeply nested checks out into
different methods. e.g. checking for the type of command that the
user input. Abstract date and time checking out as well.

For all tasks classes, removed unnecessary methods that are
repeated such as printdate and printtime, converted to use toString
method

Duke is now able to detect when a duplicate task is being entered,
if a task that already exists is entered, an error is thrown to the
user, and the task will not be added.

commitResults.messageTitle: Multiple tasks containing the same details can be added to the list of tasks, resulting in repeated/duplicated tasks.
commitResults.messageBody:
This can lead to confusion to the user when he continues to add
tasks that he thinks may not have been added yet to the list.

Let's change the Parser to check whether a task already exists
before adding it.

commitResults.messageTitle: Text in the windows were very generic and disorganized.
commitResults.messageBody:
Let's fix that by adding speech bubbles around each text, along
with background colours and a different font to change things up,
making the text more user-friendly.

commitResults.messageTitle: There is no User Guide, so new users might feel daunted and unsure of how to use this application.
commitResults.messageBody:
Let's add a user guide for our new users and guide them through on
Duke's features as well as how to use them.

1. Fixed bug for CLI print statements. Extra blank line now not
printed anymore

2. Fixed bug for storage. Now data is stored in C drive data folder
instead of a relative data path. JAR file can now store and
retrieve  the data required.
